result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley L Ontiberos was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Avoid Penalty, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(b).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Pursuant to 303.08 Work Release/Huber Privileges.

May be served in Outagamie or Winnebago County.

9:52 Defendant Ashley L Ontiberos in court with attorney Karl Alexander Schmidt.  Michael Daniel Zell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court opens without presence of jury. Motions in Limine are heard. No objection to Motions 1-5. Granted. Officer will be allowed to remain in courtroom and not subject to sequestration.  Attorney Schmidt states his position on Motion #6. No ruling on motion at this time.  No object to 7 & 8. Granted. Attorney Schmidt states position on motion #9.  No ruling at this time.  No objection to 10-14. Granted. Parties agree that defendant has 7 prior criminal convictions.  
10:00 Jury is brought into courtroom and is sworn.  
10:07 Twenty jurors are called to the box. Court begins voir dire.
10:15 Attorney Zell does voir dire.
10:32 Attorney Schmidt does voir dire.
10:39 Strikes are made and Court reads preliminary jury instructions.
10:48 Twelve jurors are sworn.
10:49 Attorney Zell gives opening statement.
10:56 Attorney Schmidt gives opening statement.
10:58 Jury in recess. Court questions parties regarding evidence that will be presented. 
11:01 Court in recess.
11:18 Court reconvenes. Attorney Schmidt objects to other bad acts. Attorney Zell makes statement.  Court will allow evidence that defendant did not have a valid driver's license.
11:25 Andrew Berg is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Zell. He is a police officer with the Nekoosa Police Department. Testifies as to his duties as a patrol officer.  He states he is always in uniform and in a marked squad when on duty. Testifies as to his training.  Testifies as to normal procedure for issuing citations.  On 5/13/15, he performed a traffic stop in the City of Nekoosa.  He ran a license plate while on patrol and the plate came back to a vehicle that was different than the vehicle that it was on.  He performed a traffic stop on the vehicle. The female driver stated she did not have any identification with her, but identified her as A.P. He issued a citation to the driver, who he believed to be A.P. and gave it to the driver.  Mid-June he received information from Officer Dhein that the person he issued the citation to was not A.P. He met with A.P. at the Nekoosa Police Department and he confirmed that she was not the person he issued the citation to. He then tried to find out who the person was that he issued the citation to. Based on investigation, the defendant was the suspected driver.  Testifies as to his investigation and concluded that defendant was the person he gave the citation to. A.P. supplied him with a phone number. He called the number and the defendant answered. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. A passenger in the vehicle at the time of the traffic stop on 5/13/15 was in the courtroom with defendant this morning.  He states that after running the defendant's driving record, she did not have a valid driver's license on 5/13/15.  
11:46 Attorney Schmidt cross-examines witness.  
11:54 Jury in recess.  Attorney Schmidt states that he has not received copy of citation.  Attorney Zell states that the officer can obtain a copy of the citation with the narrative over the lunch hour and provide it to Attorney Schmidt. 
11:58 Court in recess.
1:07 Court reconvenes. Attorney Schmidt states that he has received a copy of the citation. Court rules that defense can question officer regarding citation.
1:14 Jury is brought into courtroom. Attorney Schmidt continues cross-examining Officer Berg.
1:17 Attorney Zell redirects. 
1:20 Attorney Schmidt cross-examines witness. 
1:22 A.P. is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Zell. She states that she knows defendant and was friends with her. They also lived together. When she got a letter in mail from the Nekoosa Police Department regarding non-payment of citation, she called the Nekoosa Police Department and talked to Officer Dhein. She then met with Officer Berg at the Nekoosa Police Department. She told him that it was not her that the citation was issued to and she suspected the defendant. She states she has been convicted of a crime 7 times.
1:26 Attorney Schmidt cross-examines witness.  
1:34 Attorney Zell redirects.  
1:36 Court in recess.
1:49 Court reconvenes without presence of jury.  Attorney Schmidt states that defendant wishes to testify. Court questions defendant. She states she wishes to testify and it is her decision.  
1:51 Jury is brought into courtroom.  Ashley Ontiberos is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Schmidt.  She states that on 5/13/15, she was in Milwaukee at her boyfriend's mother's house.  She states she did not receive a phone call from Officer Berg regarding this incident. She denies that she ever claimed to be A.P. She states that there have been instances where A.P. has been mistaken for her.  She states that A.P. does know C.H. and he is the reason that they are no longer friends.  She is now dating C.H. She states she has been convicted of a crime 7 times.  
1:58 Attorney Zell cross-examines witness.  
2:00 Attorney Schmidt redirects.
2:01 Jury in recess. Defendant's prior convictions were stipulated to. Court takes judicial notice of CCAP printout of prior convictions.
2:04 Court in recess.
2:18 Court reconvenes without presence of jury. Jury instructions are reviewed. 
2:22 Jury is brought into courtroom. Court reads jury instructions.
2:37 Attorney Zell gives closing statement. 
2:49 Attorney Schmidt gives closing statement.
3:00 Attorney Zell gives closing rebuttal statement.
3:05 Court gives closing jury instructions.
3:09 Court officers Dave Hoks and Carl Lemke are sworn as court officers and jurors retire to deliberate. Court reviews prior criminal convictions of defendant and states all 7 convictions would have been allowed in.
3:10 Court in recess.
3:36 Jurors return with verdict of guilty to counts 1 & 2. Court polls the jury.  
3:41 Jury is dimissed. Attorney Zell asks Court to enter verdict and Court so enters. 
Attorney Schmidt asks for sentencing at later date. Matter will be set for later date. Bond is continued.
